The decline in economic activity through November has seen unemployment rise steadily in the Mexican state. The Instituto Nacional de Estadística y Geografía observed a rapid increase in unemployment in the first quarter, because from January to March 55,053 Sinaloans were unemployed, which corresponds to 4.53 percent of the labor force. The unemployment rate rose to 5.28 percent in the second quarter and 6.19 percent from July to September, leaving 74,000 unemployed in Sinaloa. That is 18,969 more people than in the first quarter.
Lower liquidity
