An official delegation, led by Uruguayan President José Mujica and composed of several ministers and businessmen, started its visit from Mexico on Tuesday to expand trade between the two countries and discuss political issues in the region
Mujica is meeting with his Mexican counterpart Felipe Calderón next Wednesday. That will be the culmination of his packed schedule of politicians, businessmen and a meeting with the collective of Uruguayans living in Mexico, according to the Uruguayan president.
