Guatemalan President Álvaro Colom announced Tuesday that he would authorize the extradition of former governor Alfonso Portillo to stand trial in the United States for a $70 million money laundering conspiracy.
Thus ends the trial of the United States&#39; request for Portillo&#39;s extradition to stand trial there.
In a press conference, Colom confirmed his decision was based on the independence of the judiciary and government, given that a decision-making court had already ordered the extradition.
