MSS announces research protocol to find gene for obesity
The Social Security Institute of Mexico is leading a research project to find the gene for obesity in children and adolescents, supported by specialists from the IPN.
The Instituto Mexicano del Seguro Social - IMSS (Social Security Agency of Mexico) announced that it is leading a research project to discover the gene for obesity in children and adolescents entitled &quot;Genetics of childhood and adolescent obesity&quot; to which the genetic markers will be linked to be found with overweight.
Miguel Cruz López, head of the Unidad de Investigación Médica en Bioquímica (Department of Medical Research, specializing in biochemistry) at the Hospital de Especialidades del Centro Médico Nacional Siglo XXI clinic, explained that an interdisciplinary team was set up, consisting of doctors, nurses, nutritionists and social workers became.
